title: SOCIAL AND ETHICAL ISSUES IN ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE
description: Examines social and ethical issues that arise in artificial intelligence (AI). Analyzes how AI could change the understanding of humanity, morality, and society. Evaluates decisions related to the development and use of AI, and creates moral and socially responsible decisions.
registration_restrictions: Postbac Degree Seeking or Undergraduate level students may not enroll.
